WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:05.339
** [ Blues Rock ]
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

00:11.712 --> 00:14.348
Whoa.
Move that hand
right now.

00:16.717 --> 00:20.054
** [ Continues ]

00:20.088 --> 00:22.690
Annie.
Hey, I want to read you
something.

00:22.723 --> 00:25.359
- I know how to read.
- That's great.
Here. Listen to this.

00:25.393 --> 00:27.828
What is it?
It's poetry.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.997
Aww. It's been tried,
and it's died.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.865
Shakespeare came in here
and I have to tell you,
that's old.

00:32.700 --> 00:35.203
- Next.
- Gee, you're pretty.

00:35.236 --> 00:38.606
- Very retro.
- There you go.

00:43.244 --> 00:45.246
I knew you'd come back.

00:45.279 --> 00:48.216
You better watch
those hands, buddy.
Get your hands off--

00:48.249 --> 00:51.051
- Get your hands off!
- Hey! Hey!

00:54.388 --> 00:57.191
[ Grunting ]

00:57.225 --> 00:59.560
Be a gentleman.

01:08.068 --> 01:12.206
- You paid him, right?
- Wow. You're cold.

01:12.240 --> 01:14.975
- You paid him!
- I didn't pay him,
but I would've.

01:20.248 --> 01:22.583
Yo.

01:22.616 --> 01:24.118
Why is love
like seasickness?

01:24.152 --> 01:26.220
Why?

01:26.254 --> 01:28.222
Once you got it,
you got it.

01:28.256 --> 01:30.624
[ Beeping ]

01:30.658 --> 01:32.993
Sergeant White.

01:35.929 --> 01:38.732
Ahh.

01:38.766 --> 01:41.602
Open field, mate.
Been called back to duty.

01:50.178 --> 01:54.915
Turn that damn thing off.
No light
near the open flight deck.

01:54.948 --> 01:57.951
- They're flying N.V.
- How the hell would you know?

01:58.619 --> 02:01.422
What's his problem?

02:01.455 --> 02:03.824
I don't think he likes M.P.'s.
What you writing?

02:03.857 --> 02:06.827
Poem.
Yeah? What about?

02:06.860 --> 02:09.263
Poetry.
About my bayonet.

02:09.297 --> 02:12.433
That's touching.
Is there no end
to your talents?

02:12.466 --> 02:14.968
I can't make
a very good margarita.

02:15.002 --> 02:17.471
Package is waking up.

02:17.505 --> 02:19.207
Hey! Three!

02:21.342 --> 02:26.013
- What is it?
- I don't know.
A poem, something.

02:29.317 --> 02:32.353
"Sheffield Steel.
They say love will find a way."

02:34.488 --> 02:36.957
Is it unusual for a soldier
to be a poet?

02:36.990 --> 02:39.627
We're not soldiers.
We're M.P.'s.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.629
All right, if things
go bad on the ground,

02:41.662 --> 02:44.232
put yourself
under the protection
of a combatant.

02:46.534 --> 02:48.502
How dangerous is it
down there?

02:48.536 --> 02:53.140
Well, stick by me,
Sergeants White and Blue,
you'll be fine.

02:53.173 --> 02:57.044
If it had been dangerous,
D.O.D. would've sent you in
a squad of Special Forces...

02:57.077 --> 02:59.313
or never let you come.

02:59.347 --> 03:02.350
Start putting things together.
Get the package ready.

03:21.535 --> 03:25.172
[ Announcer On P.A. ]
Please give a U.S. Army welcome
to Miss Lila Lee!

03:25.205 --> 03:27.441
[ Soldiers Cheering ]

03:42.055 --> 03:44.057
Whoo! How's everybody
doing tonight?

03:44.091 --> 03:47.528
[ Cheering Continues ]
Good!

03:47.561 --> 03:50.698
All right, y'all,
so listen.

03:50.731 --> 03:52.600
Y'all
are looking good.

03:52.633 --> 03:56.904
Um, you know,
I never met my daddy.
He died in Desert Storm.

03:56.937 --> 04:01.909
- But Mama used to say he had
this real favorite song.
- Grab him.

04:01.942 --> 04:04.545
* Oh, give me a home

04:04.578 --> 04:07.548
* Where the buffalo roam
[ Cheering, Applause ]

04:07.581 --> 04:13.887
* Where the deer
and the antelope play *

04:13.921 --> 04:17.591
Hey, I'm out of ink.
You got a pen?

04:17.625 --> 04:20.394
Now, y'all
are cowboys at heart!
Sing along with me.

04:20.428 --> 04:21.895
[ Cheering Continues ]

04:21.929 --> 04:24.465
* Where seldom is heard

04:24.498 --> 04:27.801
- * A discouraging word
- ** [ Singing Along ]

04:27.835 --> 04:30.738
* And the skies
are not clou-- *

04:30.771 --> 04:35.075
[ Cheering Intensifies ]

04:35.108 --> 04:39.747
* Please, please let me
make it right *

04:39.780 --> 04:42.750
* Let me turn down
the lights *

04:42.783 --> 04:45.953
* Please let me
latch the door *

04:45.986 --> 04:49.957
* All the kings bow before

04:51.325 --> 04:54.762
* Well, let me
hear it now *

04:54.795 --> 04:56.630
[ Soldier ]
Marry me, Lila!

04:56.664 --> 04:58.432
* Latch the door

04:58.466 --> 05:02.269
* Make it right

05:02.302 --> 05:06.273
* Let me be yours

05:06.306 --> 05:10.778
* Tonight *

05:10.811 --> 05:14.382
[ Cheering, Applause ]

05:19.653 --> 05:21.655
Whoo!

05:35.068 --> 05:38.038
Get your M.P. hands
off my pup.

05:38.071 --> 05:41.008
You killed 'em.
Yeah, I killed 'em.

05:41.041 --> 05:44.378
- I didn't even need a gun.
How about that?
- Most impressive.

05:44.412 --> 05:46.814
You think that's worth
$50 million a year?

05:46.847 --> 05:49.817
Only thing I know that's
worth that kind of money
is good manners.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.852
Kiss my ass.

05:54.354 --> 05:58.025
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

05:58.058 --> 06:01.829
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

06:01.862 --> 06:03.897
* See another dawn

06:03.931 --> 06:06.734
* Through a daughter's eyes

06:06.767 --> 06:10.203
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

06:16.710 --> 06:19.012
Bill? Company!

06:19.046 --> 06:21.915
Mr.--
Uh, Danny White.

06:21.949 --> 06:24.351
Mr. White!
Sergeant White.

06:24.384 --> 06:26.386
Guy in soft clothes!

06:26.420 --> 06:28.388
You a C.I.D.?

06:28.422 --> 06:31.391
Oh, something like that.
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.694
[ Laughs ]
You boys.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.930
Come on in,
get yourself a cup of coffee.
Thank you, ma'am.

06:36.964 --> 06:38.599
You, uh, work
with him before?

06:38.632 --> 06:40.768
- We've met.
- Where was that?

06:40.801 --> 06:43.771
He was kicking me
off my base.

06:43.804 --> 06:46.073
- Bill!
- Morning.

06:46.106 --> 06:48.576
Your wife's
a very hospitable woman.

06:48.609 --> 06:50.578
Oh, you mean
she's very perceptive.

06:50.611 --> 06:52.546
Is that what I mean?

06:52.580 --> 06:56.049
Well, she let you in here
without seeing I.D.
or a badge or anything.

06:56.083 --> 06:57.818
Maybe you mean
she's too trusting.

06:59.753 --> 07:03.891
Don't drink my wife's
good coffee and tell me
she's too trusting.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.594
- A cop's wife?
What could be worse?
- [ Snickers ]

07:06.627 --> 07:08.896
Drink up.
I'll be back in five.

07:08.929 --> 07:11.799
Oh, by the way,
I told her to expect you.

07:11.832 --> 07:14.902
I'm not due for another 15.

07:14.935 --> 07:17.738
- Well, I told her
you'd be early.
- How'd you know that?

07:17.771 --> 07:21.909
I figured you'd wanna get here,
catch me off guard, establish
dominance, like the book says.

07:21.942 --> 07:25.145
Want a piece of pie?
It's in the icebox.

07:45.666 --> 07:49.670
Just give her breakfast, son.
No autographs. You'll get these
on your way out.

07:51.639 --> 07:53.941
Miss Lee?

07:53.974 --> 07:56.143
All right.
She's up.

07:59.513 --> 08:03.617
Sergeant White,
why don't you grab some grub?

08:03.651 --> 08:07.120
"Sheffield Steel."
Young fellow's
quite the poet.

08:07.154 --> 08:10.323
Is that what he is?
Your friend's notebook.
I took the liberty.

08:10.357 --> 08:13.160
Good material
for a song or two.
Mm-hmm.

08:13.193 --> 08:16.463
Hey, she wants to go
to the forward area.

08:16.496 --> 08:18.465
This is
the forward area.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.701
She wants to be
out on patrol.

08:20.734 --> 08:22.135
Ain't gonna happen.

08:22.169 --> 08:25.305
But if she wants
the same effect,
I can blow her foot off.

08:25.338 --> 08:28.041
She wants to
"Get up in the thick of it."

08:28.075 --> 08:33.046
Sir, this right here could,
in the blinking of an eye,
be the thick of it.

08:33.080 --> 08:38.151
My orders are to ensure
her safety in this area
till 2230 this date...

08:38.185 --> 08:41.321
and pack her back on a lovely
and talented helicopter.

08:41.354 --> 08:45.225
Thence to Baghdad
and out of my hair.

08:45.258 --> 08:48.061
If she has a different plan?
Her possession of a plan
is her God-given right.

08:48.095 --> 08:50.698
But she will go
when and where she's told.

08:50.731 --> 08:53.533
Let's review
today's festivities.

08:53.567 --> 08:56.036
Ah, a publicity walk around
in one quarter-hour.

08:56.069 --> 08:58.038
[ Lila ]
Mmm. [ Giggles ]

08:58.071 --> 09:01.174
- Come here.
- [ Jonas ] Do you believe this?

09:01.208 --> 09:03.176
Hey, wanna give her
some privacy?

09:03.210 --> 09:05.713
Secure him.

09:05.746 --> 09:08.048
Come here.
[ Panting ]

09:08.081 --> 09:11.018
- [ Whining ]
- Okay, let's break that up.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.920
Could you excuse us,
please?

09:12.953 --> 09:14.554
Yeah, in a minute.

09:14.588 --> 09:16.890
Son,
you're out of uniform.

09:16.924 --> 09:20.728
Son, I'm here in an official
capacity, and that capacity
is to kick your ass.

09:20.761 --> 09:23.230
Sergeant Blue. This boy
wants a four-wall conference.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.866
- Sir!
- Sergeant White,
secure this area.

09:25.899 --> 09:29.903
- Miss, I'd like you to
put on some clothes.
- Is that so?

09:29.937 --> 09:34.207
I would've bet you
you would've liked the opposite,
a fine-looking man like you.

09:34.241 --> 09:36.243
Come on over here.
Miss, get dressed.

09:36.276 --> 09:40.047
- You're due outside to talk
to the press in 10 minutes.
- [ Scoffs ] Go get my dog.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.149
- And what's the magic word?
- Have a drink.

09:53.293 --> 09:57.430
You son of a bitch.
I offer you a drink,
and this is how you treat me?

09:57.464 --> 10:00.400
Get the hell out of here!

10:00.433 --> 10:03.971
"Kings Bow Before Me!"
Have you not heard that song?

10:04.004 --> 10:07.474
Get out of here!
Get out!

10:07.507 --> 10:11.078
- That's par for the course.
- What is she? Crazy?

10:11.111 --> 10:13.313
Yeah, she's crazy.

10:13.346 --> 10:17.785
Now, if any son of a bitch
expects me to perform
in this atmosphere,

10:17.818 --> 10:20.087
y'all are barkin'
frickin' mad!

10:20.120 --> 10:23.991
And let me tell you,
if you do not get these bozos
out of my area code,

10:24.024 --> 10:26.259
I'm staying right here...

10:26.293 --> 10:29.429
and you can take your
afternoon concert and shove it!

10:29.462 --> 10:33.433
Oh. P.S., I want to
go where the action is.

10:33.466 --> 10:35.803
I didn't come here
to sign autographs.

10:35.836 --> 10:40.173
[ Soldiers Chanting ]
Lila! Lila! Lila! Lila! Lila!

10:40.207 --> 10:43.777
Lila! Lila!
Lila! Lila!

10:43.811 --> 10:45.879
[ Hooting, Cheering ]
[ Chanting Continues ]

10:48.315 --> 10:51.785
Well, hey!
How y'all doing?
[ Cheering Continues ]

10:51.819 --> 10:56.323
I have to say it is an honor
to be here among you people.

10:56.356 --> 11:00.694
[ Mack ]
Hey, break it up!
Break it up! Back it up!

11:00.728 --> 11:04.464
Think there might be
a song lyric in that?
You got real possibilities.

11:04.497 --> 11:06.800
Really?
I said move it back!

11:06.834 --> 11:09.136
Hey!

11:09.169 --> 11:13.006
I ain't movin'
till these bozos are gone.

11:13.040 --> 11:15.375
Yeah!
[ Cheering Continues ]

11:15.408 --> 11:18.478
You know, I hate the M.P.'s.

11:18.511 --> 11:21.514
Any y'all hate the M.P.'s?
[ Soldiers Cheering ]
Yeah!

11:23.683 --> 11:26.820
- Here. You forgot
your funny little hat.
- [ Soldiers Laughing ]

11:26.854 --> 11:29.656
Show us your tattoo!

11:29.689 --> 11:32.059
[ Cheering Intensifies ]
How'd y'all hear
about that ol' tattoo?

11:32.092 --> 11:34.194
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

11:36.196 --> 11:38.565
You know, they promised
they wouldn't print that.

11:38.598 --> 11:40.667
Well, they lied to you,
sweetheart.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.402
You know what I'd like?

11:42.435 --> 11:47.174
I would love to just
purely live among you all.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.176
No, that's right.

11:49.209 --> 11:52.579
Just to be with you,
eat with you...

11:52.612 --> 11:54.581
and sleep with you.

11:54.614 --> 11:57.384
- [ Shouting Continues ]
- All right, y'all,
you know what I meant.

11:57.417 --> 11:59.753
Don't take it
the wrong way.

11:59.787 --> 12:02.355
I mean, after all,
I am a good girl.

12:02.389 --> 12:06.059
- Yeah!
- Trust me. I am a good girl.

12:06.093 --> 12:08.695
Ain't life interesting
sometimes?

12:08.728 --> 12:10.864
I've remarked that, too.

12:10.898 --> 12:13.566
[ Buzzer Buzzes ]
[ Door Unlocking ]

12:16.970 --> 12:18.571
Higgins!

12:18.605 --> 12:21.608
- Mr. Higgins,
what's the color of the day?
- Color of the day is blue.

12:21.641 --> 12:24.077
Tell me the other thing.
Rover fortune.

12:24.111 --> 12:26.713
- What's your Aunt Sarah's
maiden name?
- Hendrickson.

12:26.746 --> 12:29.883
Mr. Strickland,
what was the name of
your first music teacher?

12:29.917 --> 12:32.552
Mr. Ricardo.

12:32.585 --> 12:35.388
A lot of trouble to take
to guard a guy
that's gonna be dead.

12:35.422 --> 12:37.424
Well, we're all
gonna be dead.

12:37.457 --> 12:40.560
I assume the guy just didn't
want him to die in his custody.

12:40.593 --> 12:43.496
I'm gonna sleep a lot easier
tonight and that's the truth.
Thanks for coming.

12:49.002 --> 12:51.738
You know, I've done a lot
of prisoner transport.
All right.

12:51.771 --> 12:54.074
You want to hear
my theory?

12:54.107 --> 12:57.577
Your first music teacher
was Mr. Ricardo?
That's right.

12:57.610 --> 12:59.479
What was your instrument?
[ Laughs ]

13:06.619 --> 13:08.621
[ Beeps ]

13:20.333 --> 13:22.502
Mr. Ayoub, it's time.

13:22.535 --> 13:24.637
It's time.

13:36.149 --> 13:38.218
I'll check it out.

13:42.322 --> 13:44.457
E.T.A. stage one in--

13:44.491 --> 13:47.127
Twenty.
Stage one in 20 minutes.

13:47.160 --> 13:49.329
Yeah.

13:49.362 --> 13:52.699
[ Engine Starts ]
Hey, uh, I got
a daughter, too.

13:52.732 --> 13:56.169
- She's nine. That's her.
- What you got there?

13:56.203 --> 13:58.538
- Family picture.
- [ Chuckles ]

13:59.406 --> 14:02.042
Why are you doing that?

14:08.015 --> 14:11.184
[ Woman On P.A. ]
This is a T.S.A.
security advisory.

14:11.218 --> 14:14.154
Do not leave your car
unattended at the curb.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.689
You will be ticketed
and towed.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.878
[ Woman On P.A. Continues,
Indistinct ]

14:48.755 --> 14:52.392
Rover fortune.
Flight's delayed.

14:52.425 --> 14:55.395
- What do they want to do?
- They want you to wait.

14:55.428 --> 14:57.597
[ Bob ]
We'll put him
in the room.

15:05.072 --> 15:07.807
[ Buzz, Door Unlocks ]

15:15.949 --> 15:17.985
We got this.

15:21.454 --> 15:25.392
It's all clear here.
What are you doing, showing him
pictures of the folks back home?

15:25.425 --> 15:28.261
- Well, I have a theory
about that.
- What's its source?

15:28.295 --> 15:33.766
The source is, I've been
doing prisoner transport
for 13, 14 years.

15:33.800 --> 15:37.670
I've learned that time spent
on the bushwa is time
you ain't spending on security.

15:40.273 --> 15:43.910
And P.S., what the hell do
you care if I'm showing him
pictures of my family?

15:43.943 --> 15:45.912
What does it gain?
What's it gain?

15:45.945 --> 15:50.950
What it gains,
that fella's gonna get shot.

15:50.984 --> 15:53.253
He's got nothing to lose.

15:53.286 --> 15:56.089
What?
Is he gonna overpower you?
The fella's a zombie.

15:56.123 --> 15:58.125
He's not gonna overpower me.

15:58.158 --> 16:01.094
But he's liable,
and I speak from experience,
at any given minute,

16:01.128 --> 16:04.931
to jump
from his affectless state
into his nut bag.

16:04.964 --> 16:07.834
'Cause
basically he's nuts.

16:07.867 --> 16:10.337
He doesn't know
whether he's dead or alive.

16:10.370 --> 16:12.939
He doesn't know if he wants
to get it over with now
or live forever.

16:12.972 --> 16:15.275
And?

16:15.308 --> 16:17.610
And so if we bypass
that rationale,

16:17.644 --> 16:21.281
connect with him unconsciously
about things he's familiar with,
like a normal life,

16:21.314 --> 16:25.952
he's much more likely
to stay calm and biddable.

16:25.985 --> 16:28.455
What? Too long a speech
for the M.P.'s?

16:28.488 --> 16:30.690
He's upset
about his own daughter.

16:30.723 --> 16:33.360
He can't see his own daughter.
That's why I showed him
pictures of mine.

16:33.393 --> 16:36.129
Connect with him
on a human level.
Keeps him quiet.

16:36.163 --> 16:38.498
Watch this.

16:41.168 --> 16:44.137
I tried to
turn on the television,
but it's not working.

16:44.171 --> 16:48.041
I think they're a little afraid
you're gonna be getting messages
from Mars or something.

16:48.075 --> 16:51.211
- What's your daughter's name?
- Name's Maisy.

16:51.244 --> 16:53.012
Mine's Nali.

16:55.048 --> 16:57.350
Yes.
Leave the door open.

17:00.187 --> 17:03.723
Great. You can take him home
and keep him as a pet. Except
he's gonna be dead tomorrow.

17:03.756 --> 17:07.494
What's your mission, soldier?
Deliver the package
alive and whole.

17:07.527 --> 17:09.996
Well, advanced your goal
by another man's road.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.499
-Fella's killed a lot of people.
-And he's gonna die for it
tomorrow.

17:12.532 --> 17:15.835
What are you gonna do today
that's gonna make that
any worse? What?

17:15.868 --> 17:17.904
Talk to him
disrespectfully?

17:19.372 --> 17:21.341
We're gonna be here
for a bit.

17:21.374 --> 17:25.078
Bet you can't guess
what I got in my pocket.
No, I can't.

17:25.112 --> 17:27.547
Deck of cards.

17:33.086 --> 17:36.123
Sit down.
Sit down.

17:43.062 --> 17:46.233
My daughter
lives in this city.

17:46.266 --> 17:47.900
That's a shame.

17:51.304 --> 17:53.072
[ Knocking On Door ]

17:54.574 --> 17:56.943
Oh, thank God you've come.
Hey.

17:56.976 --> 17:59.712
Is he here?
Yes, he's here.

17:59.746 --> 18:03.283
It's so good to have a man
around the house.
What have you tried?

18:03.316 --> 18:06.553
Well, we've tried not having
a man around the house,
and that's not so good.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.556
Okay.
Is the water shut off?

18:09.589 --> 18:11.558
Oh, hi.

18:11.591 --> 18:13.926
Oh, knock it off.

18:13.960 --> 18:15.995
Kim.
Hey, Kim.

18:18.931 --> 18:21.134
Olly olly oxen free, okay?

18:21.168 --> 18:24.771
I do not need to be set up
by the Marx Brothers.

18:24.804 --> 18:27.774
And I do not need to
suffer the machinations
of the well-meaning.

18:27.807 --> 18:31.778
- You know Hector Williams?
- I've met Hector Williams,
and we've had our say.

18:31.811 --> 18:33.280
- Why not?
- Why not?

18:33.313 --> 18:35.815
- That's right.
- Why not go out with you?

18:35.848 --> 18:38.117
That's right.

18:38.151 --> 18:41.254
At least he's straightforward.
Turn it around.
Why go out with you?

18:41.288 --> 18:43.156
Because he's gaga
about you.
Dime a dozen.

18:43.190 --> 18:45.325
Because I'm a nice guy.
Nice guys finish last.

18:45.358 --> 18:48.628
Because he's drop-dead
the best soldier on the base.
Take it to the bank.

18:48.661 --> 18:52.265
Well, why didn't you
lead off with that?
That'll get you a date.

18:52.299 --> 18:54.467
Think of it what you will.

18:58.471 --> 19:02.175
- I've got her and her manager
screaming bloody murder.
- Sir, I got my hands tied.

19:02.209 --> 19:07.280
I have been directed, me
and my team, suit up as M.P.'s
because young lady, quote,

19:07.314 --> 19:10.950
"Doesn't wish to be guarded by,"
saving your presence,
"shock troops."

19:10.983 --> 19:14.487
And here we have her request
to move among the soldiers
treated with wanton disregard.

19:14.521 --> 19:19.992
Quote, "One of the world's most
prominent young artists who has
risked her life to entertain."

19:20.026 --> 19:22.695
Sir--
Now she's gonna e-mail her
senator and the news networks.

19:22.729 --> 19:24.464
Sir.
I'm listening.

19:24.497 --> 19:27.467
Two guys in a room?
All right.

19:27.500 --> 19:31.003
She's a two-bit tart
on an adventure holiday.

19:31.037 --> 19:34.807
She's a drunk and a pill head,
and I caught her in her quarters
raping a young corporal.

19:34.841 --> 19:37.377
I cannot and will not
allow her to step one foot
out of this secured area,

19:37.410 --> 19:39.512
let alone on patrol.

19:39.546 --> 19:42.014
You will not allow?

19:42.048 --> 19:43.883
Sir, you've got
an antiwar leftie lush...

19:43.916 --> 19:46.886
the Pentagon would rather
have in the accommodation
urinating out.

19:46.919 --> 19:50.890
That's why she's here,
pursuing her dream of sacrifice
and martial glory.

19:50.923 --> 19:53.993
Two old soldiers,
we're walking a thin line.

19:54.026 --> 19:57.330
Name of the line's
"Keep her happy,
but don't get her killed."

19:57.364 --> 20:01.701
- My end of things is,
"Don't get her killed."
- Then help me out with my end.

20:01.734 --> 20:05.838
Sir,
mind if I get grisly?
Say on.

20:05.872 --> 20:08.241
She's psychotic.
Play into her sense of drama.

20:08.275 --> 20:11.911
You got a soldier who's laid up,
minor wound, take him aside.

20:11.944 --> 20:14.714
He tells her,
"You're my favorite singer
in the world.

20:14.747 --> 20:18.351
My hand don't work.
Would you write me
my letter home to Mama?"

20:18.385 --> 20:22.088
You put her on the Internet
writing a poor lad's
letter to Mama.

20:22.121 --> 20:24.090
The bloggers pick it up.

20:24.123 --> 20:27.226
Worldwide publicity.
Everybody goes home happy.

20:28.595 --> 20:30.530
Sarge, you've been
out after dark.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.932
Thank you, sir.

20:32.965 --> 20:36.869
[ Explosion ]
Where's it coming from?
Can you see 'im?

20:36.903 --> 20:38.771
We're trying
to get a fix now.
Go get 'im.

20:45.412 --> 20:47.414
She was walking
to the mess tent!

20:47.447 --> 20:49.416
Where is she now?

20:49.449 --> 20:51.451
Oh, hell!

20:53.085 --> 20:54.721
Damn!

20:54.754 --> 20:57.056
Bye, baby.

20:57.089 --> 20:59.158
[ Barking ]

21:44.303 --> 21:47.607
[ Shouting ]

21:47.640 --> 21:49.476
Please help!

21:49.509 --> 21:53.012
- [ Screams ] Oh, my God!
- [ Soldier ] Come up!

21:53.045 --> 21:54.681
How's she doing?
Shook up!

21:58.985 --> 22:01.654
Let's go!

22:01.688 --> 22:04.991
[ Panting ]

22:13.866 --> 22:16.369
Pick it up!

22:16.403 --> 22:18.505
Top, I don't think
we're going anywhere!

22:25.745 --> 22:27.680
[ Groans ]

22:35.855 --> 22:40.059
Apple Six,
this is Military Police 303!

22:43.095 --> 22:48.034
Apple Six!
This is Military Police 303!
We're taking mortar fire!

22:48.067 --> 22:52.038
- What the hell did you
think you were doing?
- I wanted to go to the party.

22:52.071 --> 22:54.040
Well, you forgot
your funny hat!

22:58.578 --> 23:01.748
These two men will meet you at
the airport. You will surrender
the prisoner to no one else.

23:01.781 --> 23:04.016
Washing his hands again?

23:04.050 --> 23:06.753
You'd be washing your hands too
if you'd done what he's done.

23:06.786 --> 23:09.188
All right, let's go.
Next stop, four hours.

23:09.221 --> 23:11.858
Our people
will meet you in Miami
and oversee the transfer.

23:11.891 --> 23:13.893
It's time.

23:20.600 --> 23:22.569
My daughter
lives in this city.

23:22.602 --> 23:24.303
It's time, sir.

23:26.773 --> 23:28.140
[ Buzzer Buzzes ]

23:30.242 --> 23:32.445
And Ayoub?
Yes, it is.

23:32.479 --> 23:34.413
No one on the plane
after us?
That's correct.

23:34.447 --> 23:36.215
Sky marshals in place?

23:36.248 --> 23:38.117
That's correct.
All right, let's go.

23:39.986 --> 23:41.954
I'd like to
see my daughter.

23:49.128 --> 23:51.464
Ayoub! Ayoub!

23:51.498 --> 23:54.567
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

23:54.601 --> 23:57.904
- [ Groaning ]
- Back in the room!
Back in the room!

23:57.937 --> 24:01.307
Send the plane.
Let the plane go.
Get him back in the room.

24:01.340 --> 24:04.944
Go. Go.
[ Speaking
Foreign Language ]

24:04.977 --> 24:08.114
Not clear!
Not clear!

24:08.147 --> 24:10.750
Well, I scrubbed it
as this airport is compromised.

24:10.783 --> 24:14.120
So is the flight.
So is the arrival airport
and time.

24:14.153 --> 24:16.322
I'll hold.
It's his daughter.

24:17.524 --> 24:19.959
Is that right?
Is that your daughter?

24:22.128 --> 24:24.931
What is that?
What does that say?
Who reads that?

24:24.964 --> 24:26.966
No, no, no.
Dream on.

24:26.999 --> 24:29.101
Yes.

24:29.135 --> 24:33.339
Military transport,
as my unit suggested
in the first instance.

24:33.372 --> 24:36.308
No.
Sir, we are secure here.

24:36.342 --> 24:41.313
I suggest contact his embassy.
You arrange new transport,
this field, by military carrier.

24:41.347 --> 24:43.783
Standing by.

24:43.816 --> 24:48.855
You know how to screw up
a one-car funeral? Huh?
You make it a joint operation.

24:51.991 --> 24:53.993
So who the hell are you?

24:54.026 --> 24:56.128
I--
I've broken no law.

24:56.162 --> 24:58.865
Who are you?

24:58.898 --> 25:01.534
I brought him a message
from his daughter.

25:01.568 --> 25:05.037
And how did you know
we would be here?
I've broken no law.

25:05.071 --> 25:07.139
That's true.
But you got unlucky.

25:07.173 --> 25:11.343
How did you know
we would be here?

25:11.377 --> 25:14.814
She worked it out.
What does this say?

25:14.847 --> 25:20.152
"I love you. I miss you.
I long to see you
one last time."

25:20.186 --> 25:22.154
Where is she?

25:22.188 --> 25:25.024
She longs to see him
one last time. Where is she?
I'll make it happen.

25:27.093 --> 25:28.227
She's in the airport.

25:30.196 --> 25:31.731
All right.
Did you have
a good time?

25:31.764 --> 25:33.566
Yeah, I did.

25:33.600 --> 25:35.668
Good.

25:35.702 --> 25:38.571
Aren't you in Special Forces
or something?

25:38.605 --> 25:41.240
I'm a clerk.
Mm-hmm.

25:41.273 --> 25:44.043
But didn't they ever teach you
that you gotta
take the initiative?

25:48.781 --> 25:51.017
[ Moans ]

25:51.050 --> 25:54.120
Well, I must say--

25:56.055 --> 25:58.257
Annie! Annie!

25:58.290 --> 26:00.927
Sir?
I miss you.

26:00.960 --> 26:03.596
- I got no quarrels
with you, man. Annie!
- Billy!

26:03.630 --> 26:06.532
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

26:06.565 --> 26:08.400
Now run!

26:10.236 --> 26:14.573
- You pay him?
- [ Both Laughing ]

26:19.111 --> 26:22.715
Thank you
for a lovely evening.

26:22.749 --> 26:24.717
Oh, but uh-uh.

26:24.751 --> 26:26.753
Why not?

26:26.786 --> 26:28.955
Trouble follows you!
Trouble follows me?

26:28.988 --> 26:30.957
- Uh-huh. That's right.
- Hmm.

26:30.990 --> 26:33.092
[ Laughs ]

26:44.103 --> 26:46.472
Roger that.

26:48.274 --> 26:50.276
Rest of the cavalry
in 10 to 15!

26:58.484 --> 27:00.987
There you are.
[ Gunfire, Explosions Continue ]

27:01.020 --> 27:03.089
Hey, Soldier.
How you doing?

27:03.122 --> 27:06.292
- I'm all shot up.
- You're gonna pull through!

27:11.463 --> 27:13.766
- They're on their way.
You heard that.
- Could you do something for me?

27:13.800 --> 27:15.334
Well, you bet.

27:16.836 --> 27:18.504
Would you write to my mother?

27:20.339 --> 27:23.442
What do you want me
to say to your mom?

27:23.475 --> 27:26.946
Tell her I'm with you.
She won't believe it.

27:26.979 --> 27:28.948
[ Laughing ]

27:28.981 --> 27:31.117
- Do you know my songs?
- Yeah.

27:31.150 --> 27:33.452
I know all your songs.

27:33.485 --> 27:35.287
Well, which one's your favorite?

27:35.321 --> 27:41.961
* Babe, baby, baby

27:41.994 --> 27:46.365
- [ Laughs ]
- That's my favorite, too.

27:46.398 --> 27:50.970
You want me to sing
a little for you?

27:51.003 --> 27:54.340
[ Gunfire,
Explosions Continue ]

28:03.349 --> 28:05.684
- He's sleeping?
- He's dead.

28:09.188 --> 28:10.522
We got some help!

28:12.224 --> 28:15.728
Over here!
303rd M.P.'s!

28:15.762 --> 28:19.665
Three of us and the girl,
one of yours!

28:19.698 --> 28:22.001
Come on, now.
Come on, miss.

28:22.034 --> 28:24.336
Let's move!
[ Soldiers Shouting ]

28:24.370 --> 28:27.339
Come on now, miss.
Gotta make a move.

28:27.373 --> 28:29.075
[ Mack ]
Guy coming in!

28:29.108 --> 28:30.910
[ Soldier ]
Marker six!

28:32.444 --> 28:34.546
He's dead.

28:37.216 --> 28:39.218
Let's go.
Let's make a move!

28:54.233 --> 28:56.936
Miss Lee?
Come in.

28:59.271 --> 29:01.407
The young fella...
got killed.

29:01.440 --> 29:03.409
Yes.

29:03.442 --> 29:05.411
He was running to his truck.

29:05.444 --> 29:07.546
Yes.
Why?

29:07.579 --> 29:09.481
- He went back for ammunition.
- [ Scoffs ]

29:17.289 --> 29:19.391
Your man.
Yes.

29:19.425 --> 29:21.227
- Ran out to get him.
- Yes.

29:21.260 --> 29:23.429
Why?

29:23.462 --> 29:25.464
Go ahead and drink
if you have to.

29:25.497 --> 29:29.101
I was gonna say
it won't kill you,
but it will kill you.

29:29.135 --> 29:30.669
It just takes its time.

29:33.272 --> 29:36.442
[ Coughing ]

29:36.475 --> 29:38.477
Top.

29:40.779 --> 29:45.784
Hey. D.F.I. Troop's full of
healthy anticipation waiting
for our friend to sing.

29:45.818 --> 29:50.089
Post which immediate evac by
helo to Baghdad and then to the
world, not sparing the horses.

29:50.122 --> 29:53.125
- Security by other troops
and we are stood down.
- Lila!

29:53.159 --> 29:55.594
She's in back.
I'm not sure
if she'll sing.

29:55.627 --> 29:58.998
And if not,
I'd like to pack her up
and get her out right now.

29:59.031 --> 30:01.767
- I'll ask her.
I'll ask her for you.
- [ Scoffs ]

30:01.800 --> 30:05.471
Look, Sergeant said
he's gonna ask her.

30:07.639 --> 30:09.775
[ Jonas ]
They're hoping
you'll sing 'em a song.

30:09.808 --> 30:11.610
They expect me to sing?
That's right.

30:11.643 --> 30:14.780
After what just happened?
You wanted to come and sing.

30:14.813 --> 30:17.483
Information on the soldier.
You said you'd write him
a letter.

30:21.653 --> 30:23.555
Thank you.

30:24.857 --> 30:27.659
- I'll go out there and sing.
- That's right.

30:31.864 --> 30:34.333
- Do you believe
people can change?
- No.

30:40.907 --> 30:44.643
You don't believe
that people can change?

30:44.676 --> 30:47.713
Nope.
Seen it though.

30:51.517 --> 30:54.153
How did you know your father
would be here?
Where else would he be?

30:54.186 --> 30:55.821
Explain it
to my satisfaction.

30:55.854 --> 30:58.357
Is my father here?
Just break it down.

30:58.390 --> 31:01.493
I want to see my father.
You help me,
I'll help you.

31:01.527 --> 31:05.064
I don't believe you.
Well, you don't help me, I don't
help you. You can believe that.

31:05.097 --> 31:08.667
- You needed to take him
on a commercial flight.
- And why is that?

31:08.700 --> 31:10.903
To show that he is
not a military prisoner,
which he is.

31:10.937 --> 31:13.172
He--
To show your hands
are clean.

31:13.205 --> 31:15.674
He is a civilian prisoner
of the Federal Department
of Prisons,

31:15.707 --> 31:18.844
which is remanding him
to the government
of your country for trial.

31:18.877 --> 31:21.547
He is going to be
executed tomorrow.

31:22.915 --> 31:25.084
Things are rough all over.

31:28.387 --> 31:30.056
She's alone.
Airport's clean.

31:31.257 --> 31:33.259
Who's your friend?

31:33.292 --> 31:35.027
Fella with the photograph?

31:35.061 --> 31:38.364
He is my husband.

31:38.397 --> 31:41.400
- Close that door.
What are you doing?
- Papa!

31:41.433 --> 31:44.603
Nali! Nali!
Wait. Just wait.

31:48.240 --> 31:50.909
- For God's sake,
give 'em a minute.
- Why?

31:50.943 --> 31:53.379
- Out of human decency?
- Try again.

31:53.412 --> 31:56.382
- What does it cost ya?
- What do I gain from it?
Take her away.

31:56.415 --> 31:59.751
Wait! What do you
gain from it?
That's right.

31:59.785 --> 32:02.454
Do you have a family?
I can't remember.

32:02.488 --> 32:05.958
You gain that, all rhetoric
aside, all bull aside,

32:05.992 --> 32:08.627
everything he's done aside,
he's still a human being.

32:16.268 --> 32:19.305
You got a woman
on your team?
That's right.

32:19.338 --> 32:21.940
Throw a wand on her.
Search her to the skin.

32:21.974 --> 32:24.610
She's got one minute,
all of us in the room.

32:26.278 --> 32:27.746
- So.
- [ Annie ] So?

32:27.779 --> 32:30.649
Yes.

32:30.682 --> 32:33.986
- Are my actions fodder for
some round table discussion?
- Theoretically, yes.

32:34.020 --> 32:36.255
- Because?
- Well, here's why.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.257
The guy is nuts about you.

32:38.290 --> 32:41.827
It seems you
like him so, too, and--

32:41.860 --> 32:46.098
And we, our unit--

32:46.132 --> 32:48.267
- The Logistical Studies Unit.
- That's right.

32:48.300 --> 32:50.269
Have--

32:50.302 --> 32:52.938
We have--
We have certain requirements.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.806
I understand.

32:54.840 --> 32:57.309
Which do not weigh so heavily
on the married folks.

32:57.343 --> 32:59.345
All right.

32:59.378 --> 33:03.682
But which impose
certain restrictions
on the unmarried.

33:03.715 --> 33:06.485
As to
what they can tell whom.
Good for you.

33:06.518 --> 33:08.654
- Hector.
- Hector...

33:08.687 --> 33:10.689
is a gem beyond price.

33:10.722 --> 33:13.025
He is smitten with you.

33:13.059 --> 33:18.464
Where this might go,
of course you can say,
and Lord, you make me feel old.

33:18.497 --> 33:22.368
And you are in butterfly stage
of your development...

33:22.401 --> 33:25.971
and perhaps flit
from flower to flower, but--

33:26.004 --> 33:27.973
But--
if you are looking...

33:28.006 --> 33:31.643
or foresee at some point
you might be looking
for a good man--

33:31.677 --> 33:35.147
- Whatever the commitment is.
- I'm honored you think me
worthy of him.

33:35.181 --> 33:37.383
Then take a look
at Hector Williams.

33:39.385 --> 33:41.520
I'll give him one weekend.

33:43.055 --> 33:46.392
* Now, what can I say

33:46.425 --> 33:49.661
* What did I do

33:49.695 --> 33:52.498
* Was there something
you thought *

33:52.531 --> 33:56.368
* I was withholding
from you *

33:56.402 --> 33:59.371
* Help me to see

33:59.405 --> 34:02.674
* Explain it to me

34:02.708 --> 34:09.581
* Oh, baby
please come home again *

34:09.615 --> 34:16.422
* Now, I've heard that men
crave adventure *

34:16.455 --> 34:23.195
* So I'll tell you
what I have arranged *

34:23.229 --> 34:27.866
* If you left
'cause you needed *

34:27.899 --> 34:30.436
* A different girl

34:30.469 --> 34:36.608
* Come home and you'll find
that I've changed *

34:36.642 --> 34:43.715
* Oh, my latchstring
is out of the old front door *

34:43.749 --> 34:46.785
* And the staircase
still creaks *

34:46.818 --> 34:50.122
* Like it used to before

34:50.156 --> 34:53.725
* Old candlewick spread

34:53.759 --> 34:56.728
* So fine on the bed

34:56.762 --> 35:04.102
* Oh, baby, please
come home again *

35:04.136 --> 35:06.905
* It's the same old key

35:06.938 --> 35:10.576
* 'Neath the welcome mat

35:10.609 --> 35:14.146
* And an empty hook

35:14.180 --> 35:16.748
* For your traveling hat

35:16.782 --> 35:20.319
* I watch and I pray

35:20.352 --> 35:23.589
* That you'll know
the way *

35:23.622 --> 35:30.462
* Oh, baby
please come home again *

35:30.496 --> 35:34.099
* I watch and I pray

35:34.132 --> 35:36.935
* That you'll know the way

35:36.968 --> 35:40.772
* Oh, baby, please

35:40.806 --> 35:46.812
* Come home again *

35:46.845 --> 35:49.948
[ Soldiers Cheering,
Applauding ]

35:49.981 --> 35:54.853
And my dearest wish is that
you all make it home safe too.
God bless you.

36:02.027 --> 36:03.962
[ Jonas ]
What?

36:03.995 --> 36:06.131
They took my poetry book!

36:06.164 --> 36:08.200
- What?
- My poetry book!

36:12.037 --> 36:14.973
"Sheffield Steel!"
I was writing a poem!

36:15.006 --> 36:17.309
Poetry's
for sissies!

36:17.343 --> 36:20.312
What?
He said poetry's
for sissies!

36:20.346 --> 36:23.315
Did you miss
grade school, boy?
What?

36:23.349 --> 36:26.318
[ Laughs ]
He said, did you miss
grade school?

36:26.352 --> 36:30.656
No, I went!
I didn't pay attention!

36:30.689 --> 36:33.825
[ Together ]
That's why you ended up
in the army!

36:33.859 --> 36:35.594
[ Laughing ]

36:56.214 --> 36:59.017
[ Sobbing ]

36:59.050 --> 37:01.119
We have an inbound flight
touchdown in 10.

37:03.289 --> 37:06.392
[ Sobbing Continues ]

37:21.940 --> 37:23.575
[ Speaking
Foreign Language ]
No. English only.

37:25.311 --> 37:28.246
Papa?

37:28.280 --> 37:30.248
I want to--

37:31.917 --> 37:34.219
I want to say--
Shh.

37:34.252 --> 37:36.254
It's okay.

37:36.288 --> 37:38.590
Yes.
That's affirmative.
Gotta go.

37:46.131 --> 37:49.568
- You'll hold her?
- Yeah, we'll hold her.

37:49.601 --> 37:52.304
Good-bye.
[ Foreign Language ]

37:52.338 --> 37:54.139
[ Sobbing Continues ]

38:03.281 --> 38:05.016
Keep the door open.

38:06.352 --> 38:10.288
All right, let's go.
Baggage area to air-side.

38:10.322 --> 38:14.326
Van to the runway.
Put a vest on.

38:14.360 --> 38:18.096
You did the right thing.

38:18.129 --> 38:21.099
Put the vest on him.
Let's get him out of here.

38:21.132 --> 38:22.801
Where's her scarf?

38:24.202 --> 38:26.171
Where is her purple scarf?

38:29.140 --> 38:31.309
Oh, God.

38:33.645 --> 38:36.615
We need an ambulance!
We need a medic right now!
He's dead.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.650
We need a defibrillator!
He's dead.

38:44.823 --> 38:46.658
Well, she just
killed her father.

38:47.993 --> 38:50.396
She just poisoned
her father.

38:52.664 --> 38:55.534
No, don't you touch him.
I gotta make some calls.

38:55.567 --> 38:58.336
[ Officer On Headset,
Indistinct ]

39:06.678 --> 39:09.648
- You could use
a shave, soldier.
- I just got in.

39:09.681 --> 39:13.819
- What happened to "No excuses"?
Didn't they teach you that?
- No excuse, sir.

39:13.852 --> 39:16.722
You're reporting
a dead war criminal...

39:16.755 --> 39:19.024
five hours
from a happy extradition,

39:19.057 --> 39:21.359
dead on your hands
in an American airport?

39:21.393 --> 39:24.329
- Sir, that is correct.
- We did a piss-poor job
of protecting him.

39:24.362 --> 39:26.832
As instructed.

39:26.865 --> 39:29.835
We couldn't have
let him go home.
No, sir.

39:29.868 --> 39:32.170
We're clean?
Yes, sir.

39:32.203 --> 39:34.072
You're sure?
Yes, sir.

39:34.105 --> 39:36.374
Well done.

39:36.408 --> 39:39.745
Though I-- I practically
had to drag that girl
into the safe room.

39:39.778 --> 39:41.713
Dismissed.

39:43.381 --> 39:46.618
- Sir?
- All right.

39:48.219 --> 39:51.189
That M.P.
Yes?

39:51.222 --> 39:54.392
He has a daughter too.
Yes?

39:54.426 --> 39:56.562
It's gonna cost him his career.

39:58.263 --> 39:59.931
There's a war on.

40:02.133 --> 40:03.735
Top, check this out.

40:05.737 --> 40:07.539
My new song was
very much influenced...

40:07.573 --> 40:10.442
by my experiences in Iraq
three months ago.

40:10.476 --> 40:13.044
That's right.
You went to Iraq
to entertain the troops.

40:13.078 --> 40:15.046
That's right, Nigel.
Why?

40:15.080 --> 40:18.383
Why? You know, my daddy
died in Desert Storm.

40:18.416 --> 40:21.587
Come on. That's a lie.
Your daddy's a 60-year-old drunk
in Boca Raton.

40:21.620 --> 40:23.622
That's true?
That's the gospel, baby.

40:23.655 --> 40:27.593
You know, I sat with him.
I don't know if you know this,
but I was involved in-- in--

40:27.626 --> 40:29.895
In combat?
That's right.

40:29.928 --> 40:32.430
[ Jonas ]
I don't know how
they get away with this.

40:32.464 --> 40:35.601
I thought
she was, you know,
under house arrest.

40:35.634 --> 40:38.103
I think she's been
in every rehab--
Why are you so upset?

40:38.136 --> 40:41.607
Wait.
Shh-shh-shh.
** [ Guitar ]

